itermProj Opener
version 0.1
written by Jared Grippe

The iterm project opener is just a simple apple script that app that can be setup as
the default app for .itermProj files. 

.itermPorj files are just yaml files that look like this

  --- 
  - :session: Default
    :name: Logs
    :cmd: cd ~/my_rails_app && tail -n 0 -f log/*.log
  - :session: Default
    :name: Console
    :cmd: cd ~/my_rails_app && ./script/console

these yaml files are then passed onto a ruby scrip that tell iterm to open x tabs in
the above configurations.


INSTALL

git clone git://github.com/deadlyicon/Iterm-Project-Opener.git
mv Iterm-Project-Opener/ItermProjectOpener.app /Applications/
open Iterm-Project-Opener
# get info on sample.itermProj
# set Open With to ItermProjectOpener.app
# hit Change All
# sample.itermProj